                <li>
                  <b>Age of the Wall Heater </b>
                  <p>The age of your wall heater is a significant factor in deciding whether to repair or replace it. Most wall heaters have a lifespan of around 10-15 years. If your unit is nearing or has surpassed this age range, it may be more cost-effective to replace it. Older units are less efficient and more prone to frequent breakdowns, which can lead to higher repair costs over time.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Frequency and Cost of Repairs </b>
                  <p>Evaluate how often your wall heater requires repairs and the associated costs. If you find yourself frequently calling for repairs and the cumulative costs are adding up, it might be more economical to invest in a new unit. A one-time replacement cost can be more manageable than continuous repair expenses.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Energy Efficiency </b>
                  <p>Newer wall heaters are generally more energy-efficient than older models. If your current unit is inefficient and contributes to high energy bills, replacing it with a modern, energy-efficient model can save you money in the long run. Look for heaters with high Energy Star ratings to ensure optimal efficiency.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Safety Concerns </b>
                  <p>Safety is paramount when it comes to heating appliances. If your wall heater has issues that pose safety risks, such as gas leaks, faulty wiring, or signs of rust and corrosion, it's crucial to consider replacement over repair. Modern units come with enhanced safety features that can provide peace of mind.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Performance and Comfort</b>
                  <p>Assess the performance and comfort provided by your wall heater. If it struggles to maintain consistent temperatures or fails to adequately heat your space, it might be time for an upgrade. A new, well-functioning heater can provide better comfort and improved air quality.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
